  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Burgundy and Oregon Pinot Noir?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Burgundy Pinot Noir typically shows more earthiness, minerality, and restraint with notes of cherry, forest floor, and wet leaves, while Oregon Pinot Noir tends to be more fruit-forward with darker berry flavors and spice. The limestone-rich soils of Burgundy create wines with higher acidity and more structure, whereas Oregon's volcanic and sedimentary soils produce rounder, more approachable wines. Price-wise, quality Burgundy commands significantly higher prices due to limited production and historical prestige.</p>
