    <p class="text-gray-700">Premium Pinot Noir pairs beautifully with duck, salmon, mushroom risotto, and aged cheeses due to its medium body and earthy undertones. The wine's natural acidity cuts through rich dishes while its delicate tannins won't overpower lighter proteins like pork tenderloin or roasted chicken. For Burgundy specifically, try it with coq au vin or beef bourguignon, while fruit-forward New World styles complement grilled lamb or dark chocolate desserts.</p>
